article.description: — Jasin Sinani scored 14 points as Campbell beat N.C. A&T 64-62 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Sinani scores 14, Campbell takes down N.C. A&T 64-62
article.linkText: Sinani scores 14, Campbell takes down N.C. A&T 64-62
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- — Jasin Sinani scored 14 points as Campbell beat N.C. A&T 64-62 on Saturday night. Sinani added 11 rebounds for the Fighting Camels (14-17, 8-10 Coastal Athletic Association). Anthony Dell'Orso added 14 points while shooting 6 for 14, including 2 for 4 from beyond the arc, and had seven rebounds. Laurynas Vaistaras had 13 points and shot 5 for 8, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc. The Aggies (7-24, 5-13) were led in scoring by Camian Shell, who finished with 22 points and six assists. Jalal McKie added 21 points and eight rebounds for N.C. A&T. Nikolaos Chitikoudis also had 10 points, nine rebounds and two blocks. The Aggies extended their losing streak to nine straight. Gediminas Mokseckas put up eight points in the first half for Campbell, who went into halftime tied 33-33 with N.C. A&T. Tasos Cook's layup with 2:47 left in the second half gave Campbell the lead for good at 60-59. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
